# Asha secrets — example template.
#
# This file is a template — the block-secrets hook prevents writing
# real .env files, so the suffix is intentionally absent.
#
# To use:
#   1. Copy to ~/.asha/secrets.env (note the .env suffix on the destination)
#   2. chmod 600 ~/.asha/secrets.env
#   3. Fill in real values
#
# This file documents which env vars Asha skills look up. The actual values
# live OUTSIDE the asha repo at ~/.asha/secrets.env (gitignored, user-scope).
# When you add a new integration that needs a token, add a placeholder line
# here so the inventory stays accurate.
#
# These vars are loaded ONLY when launching via the asha wrapper
# (asha-claude / asha-codex), not in the user's bare shell. See
# docs/secrets.md for the rationale.
#
# Format: dotenv. KEY=VALUE per line. Values are NOT shell-expanded.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# admin/todoist
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Personal Todoist API token. Get from:
#   https://todoist.com/app/settings/integrations/developer
# Used by the admin/todoist skill for create/update/find/complete operations.
# Priority is inverted from the UI in the API: 4=p1 (highest), 1=p4 (default).
TODOIST_API_TOKEN=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# admin/gemini
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Gemini API key for grounded web search with citations.
# Get from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# Default model gemini-2.5-flash; pro available when needed.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# admin/bookstack
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BookStack self-hosted wiki. Token is combined "id:secret" — get both halves
# from BookStack → Edit Profile → API Tokens, then concatenate with a colon.
# Base URL must include "/api" suffix, no trailing slash.
BOOKSTACK_BASE_URL=
BOOKSTACK_API_TOKEN=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# admin/wolfram
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Wolfram|Alpha App ID for the LLM API (computational/factual answers).
# Get from: https://developer.wolframalpha.com/portal/myapps/ (select LLM API).
# Free non-commercial tier ~2000 calls/month. Looks like "ABCDEF-GHIJKLMNOP".
WOLFRAM_APP_ID=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Future integrations — uncomment and fill when adding the corresponding skill
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# (none currently planned — add lines here as new admin/* skills land)
